prediction function that uses K-nearest neighbors to predict the PVREAD

2.a Construct a distance_cance_sance function between students based on the student level variables. Construct a second distance_cance_sance function between students based on class-level variables. The distance_cance_sances should not include the PVREAD variable

#Make an two distance functions  as an helper functions for later using in knn algo for predicting the pvread
#euclideandistance_c for student  data dist
euclideandistance_c <- function(data_t=df_pisa_withna,other){
  #select the col from the data of pisa with na 
  data_t_wo_lang <-  select(data_t,EFFORT1, AGE, PAREDINT,DURECEC,ESCS,JOYREAD)
  #scale the data that was choosen
  scale_data<-scale(data_t_wo_lang)
  #make this data frame
  data_t<-data.frame(scale_data,data_t$LANGN)
  names(data_t)[7]<- "LANGN"
  #Extract the the attribute of the center scaled from the data
  centers<- attr(scale_data,"scaled:center")
  #Extract the the attribute of the scale scaled from the sd of the data
  sds<-attr(scale_data,"scaled:scale" )
  #Select the col from the data
  other_wo_lang_org <-  select(other,EFFORT1, AGE, PAREDINT,DURECEC,ESCS,JOYREAD)
  #Use sweep fuction for apply the data for difference  the data
  other_wo_lang_sweep = sweep(other_wo_lang_org,centers,MARGIN = 2)
  #Use sweep fuction for apply the data for divde  the data
  other_wo_lang <- sweep(other_wo_lang_sweep,sds,MARGIN = 2,"/")
  other <- data.frame(other_wo_lang,other$LANGN)
  names(other)[7]<- "LANGN"
  #Initialize the matrix for looping with 0 
  distance_cance_s <- matrix(0,nrow= nrow(data_t),ncol = nrow(other))
  keep = data_t$LANGN
  for(j in 1:nrow(other)){
    #For loop to find all the points that are inequal and add 1
    data_t$LANGN[data_t$LANGN != other$LANGN[j]] <- as.numeric(other$LANGN)[j]+1
    for (i in 1:nrow(data_t)) {
      #Cacluate the dist with mse on the the comparing data point
      distance_cance_s[i,j]<-mean(as.numeric((data_t[i,]-other[j,])^2),na.rm = TRUE)
      }
    #Restart the varible
      data_t$LANGN=keep   
}
  return(distance_cance_s)
}

#euclideandistance_c_2 for class  data dist
euclideandistance_c_2 <- function(data_t=df_pisa_withna,other){
  #select the col from the data of pisa with na 
  data_t <- 
    select(data_t,System,DISCLIMA,TEACHSUP,STRATIO,TOTAT,CLSIZE,EDUSHORT,STAFFSHORT)
  train_data_wo_sys <- 
    select(data_t,DISCLIMA,TEACHSUP,STRATIO,TOTAT,CLSIZE,EDUSHORT,STAFFSHORT)
  #scale the data that was choosen
  scale_data<-scale(train_data_wo_sys)
  #make this data frame
  data_t<-data.frame(scale_data,data_t$System)
  names(data_t)[8]<- "System"
  #Extract the the attribute of the center scaled from the data
  centers<- attr(scale_data,"scaled:center")
  #Extract the the attribute of the scale scaled from the sd of the data
  sds<-attr(scale_data,"scaled:scale" )
  #Select the col from the data
  other_wo_sys <-   select(other,DISCLIMA,TEACHSUP,STRATIO,TOTAT,CLSIZE,EDUSHORT,STAFFSHORT)
  #Use sweep fuction for apply the data for difference  the data
  other_wo_sys<-sweep(other_wo_sys,centers,MARGIN = 2)
  #Use sweep fuction for apply the data for divde  the data
  other_wo_sys<-sweep(other_wo_sys,sds,MARGIN = 2,"/")
  other <- data.frame(other_wo_sys,other$System)
  names(other)[8]<- "System"
  #Initialize the matrix for looping with 0 
  distance_c <- matrix(0,nrow= nrow(data_t),ncol = nrow(other))
  keep = data_t$System
  for(j in 1:nrow(other)){
    data_t$System[data_t$System != other$System[j]] <- 1
    data_t$System[data_t$System == other$System[j]] <- 0
    other$System[j]=0
    for (i in 1:nrow(data_t)) {
        #Cacluate the dist with mse on the the comparing data point
      distance_c[i,j]<-mean((as.numeric(data_t[i,])-as.numeric(other[j,]))^2,na.rm = TRUE)
    }
    #Restart the varible
    data_t$System=keep
    }
  return(distance_c)
}

2.b

Write a function that returns a K-nearest-neighbors prediction based on the distance_cance functions. Do not use pre-existing libraries

#Making an knn algo function that use the dists function and the data with the na and other data point with k values

knn_algo<- function(k ,dist1 ,dist2 ,alpha,train_data = df_pisa_withna,other ){
  other_student <- select(other,EFFORT1,AGE,LANGN,PAREDINT,DURECEC,ESCS,JOYREAD)
  other_class <- select(other,System,DISCLIMA,TEACHSUP,STRATIO,TOTAT,CLSIZE,EDUSHORT,STAFFSHORT)
  dist1=dist1(data_t=train_data,other=other_student)
  dist2 = dist2(data_t = train_data, other=other_class)
  #Using the formula from the instructions 
  dist <- (alpha*dist1+(1-alpha)*dist2)
  #Apply on the data order form the col
  dist_order<-apply(dist, 2,order)
  #dist_order_data = matrix(rep(train_data$PVREAD,nrow(other)),ncol = nrow(other))
  pred = c(1:nrow(other))
  for(i in 1:nrow(other)){
    ind = dist_order[1:k,i]
    pred[i] = mean(train_data$PVREAD[ind])
  }

  return(pred)
}

c. Write two functions that estimate out-of-sample prediction for different Ks and different as using cross validation. The first should use uniform subsampling to the train and test sets. In the second, the split should be according to classes

alpha_k <- expand.grid(c(1,10,60),c(0.2,0.6,0.8))

names(alpha_k)<- c("k","alpha")
alpha_k_simple <- function(alpha_k,knn_algo , data){
  set.seed(15)
  data_sample <-data[sample(1:nrow(data)),]
  train_data <- data_sample[1:4200,]
  test_data <- data_sample[4201:5543,]
  for(i in 1:nrow(alpha_k)){
    y_hat <- knn_algo(k=alpha_k$k[i],dist1 = euclideandistance_c, dist2 = euclideandistance_c_2,alpha =alpha_k$alpha[i], train_data = train_data, other = test_data)
    alpha_k$RMSE_student[i] <- sqrt(mean((y_hat-test_data$PVREAD)^2))
    print(alpha_k$RMSE_student[i])
    alpha_k$sd_student[i] <- sd(test_data$PVREAD)
  }
}



alpha_k_hard<- function(alpha_k,knn_algo, data){
  set.seed(2837)
  data_group= add_group_indices(data,c("DISCLIMA","TEACHSUP","STRATIO","TOTAT","CLSIZE","EDUSHORT","STAFFSHORT"),"group_id")
  
  train_gorups =sample(1:length(unique(data_group$group_id)),round(length(unique(data_group$group_id))*0.85))
  selected_class = data_group[data_group$group_id %in% train_gorups,]
  test_class = data_group[!(data_group$group_id %in% train_gorups),]
  for(i in 1:nrow(alpha_k)){
    y_hat <- knn_algo(k=alpha_k$k[i],dist1 = euclideandistance_c, dist2 = euclideandistance_c_2,alpha=alpha_k$alpha[i], train_data = selected_class, other = test_class)
    alpha_k$RMSE_calss[i] <- sqrt(mean((y_hat-test_class$PVREAD)^2))
    print(alpha_k$RMSE_calss[i])
    alpha_k$sd_class[i] <- sd(test_class$PVREAD)
  }
}

3

Build a prediction model for the estimated reading level (PVREAD). You can use any model you like. The goal is to get good predictions. Please

#Making rmse fuction for caculting 

RMSE = function(m, o){
  sqrt(mean((m - o)^2))
}

#Caculate the lm model functions
lm_my_prediction_model<- function(data){
  #Make dummy variable  for LANGN,System
  data_dummy <-dummy_cols(data, select_columns = c("LANGN","System"),remove_first_dummy = TRUE)
  #Remove extra cols
  data_dummy <- select(data_dummy, -c(LANGN,System))
  #Model LM reg and fill the na with mean values
  model<- lm(PVREAD~. ,data=na_mean(data_dummy))
  pred <- model$fitted.values
  #Make plot of predictions  of the model
  plot(pred, data_dummy$PVREAD,main="LM Regression prediction",ylab = "Predictions",xlab = "Data")
  #Make plot of residuals  of the predictions
  plot(model$residuals,main="LM Regression residuals")
  paste("RMSE of LM Regression",RMSE(pred,data_dummy$PVREAD))
}

#Caculate the elastic net model functions
elasticnet_my_prediction_model<- function(data){
  #Make dummy variable  for LANGN,System
  data_dummy <-dummy_cols(data, select_columns = c("LANGN","System"),remove_first_dummy = TRUE)
   #Remove extra cols
  data_dummy <- select(na_mean(data_dummy), -c(LANGN,System))
  #Cross validation with glmnet with the data_dummy fill the na with mean values
  lambda <- cv.glmnet(y=data_dummy$PVREAD,x=as.matrix(select(data_dummy,-PVREAD)),alpha = 0.5 )
   #Elastic Net with glmnet with the data_dummy fill the na with mean values
  model<- glmnet(y=data_dummy$PVREAD,x=as.matrix(na_mean(select(data_dummy,-PVREAD))),alpha = 0.5,lambda = lambda$lambda.min)
  #predict with the model and fill the na with mean values
  pred <- predict(model, newx =na_mean(as.matrix(select(data_dummy,-PVREAD))))
  #Make plot of predictions  of the model
  plot(pred, data$PVREAD,main="Elastic Net Regression prediction",ylab = "Predictions",xlab = "Data")
  #Make plot of residuals  of the predictions
  plot(pred-data$PVREAD,main="Elastic Net Regression residuals",ylab ="residuals",xlab = "Data")
  return(paste("RMSE of Elastic Net Regression",RMSE(pred,data$PVREAD)))
}

my_prediction_model<- function(data, model=model.lm){
  data_dummy <-dummy_cols(data, select_columns = c("LANGN","System"),remove_first_dummy = TRUE)
  data_dummy <- select(data_dummy, -c(LANGN,System))  
  pred <- predict(model,newx = na_mean(data_dummy))
  return(pred)
}
